        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 6:06PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 606 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles south of Hazelton, or 9 miles north of Linton, moving southeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Linton and Temvik.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
